'''''NM-KO 28''''' was a private [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] stolen by [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]] and [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] during the latter's rescue of the former from the [[CorDuro Shipping]] office on the [[Space station/Legends|orbital city]] [[Bburru Station]]. They landed it at the [[Gateway]] refugee camp on [[Duro/Legends|Duro]] and were told by their mother, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], to use it to escape the [[Duro system/Legends|Duro system]] prior to [[Battle of Duro (Yuuzhan Vong War)|the impending Yuuzhan Vong attack]], along with [[Randa Besadii Diori]]. The two of them refused to leave without Leia, or her [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]] [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguard]] [[Olmahk]]. Jaina followed her mother's example in staying at the refugee camp and eventually loaded up ''NM-KO 28'' with refugees and sent it away without Randa, her brother, Olmahk, or her mother when the initial [[Yuuzhan Vong]] invasion force, led by [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]], entered the system. Upon witnessing the Yuuzhan Vong's destruction of shuttles evacuating the orbital city [[Orr-Om]], Jaina salved her moral qualms against stealing ''NM-KO 28'' by speculating that the shuttle would have met a similar fate had she and Jacen left it on Bburru. The shuttle was equipped with a [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]], and in Jacen's opinion, could accommodate four or five passengers.

